<COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">Yugoslav President Vojislav Kostunica</COREF> has visited <COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">a tense region near the Serbian - Kosovo border , which has been the scene of deadly attacks by ethnic Albanian separatists</COREF> .
<COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">Mr. Kostunica</COREF> arrived in the town of Beonovach late Monday and was welcomed by hundreds of people .
<COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">The Yugoslav leader</COREF> pledged to bring peace to <COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">the area where an increase in fighting last week between the Albanian guerillas and Serbian security forces left four police officers dead</COREF> .
